me":"Albert","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Albert</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rhiwallon Fychan ap Rhywallon Llwyd was born about 1219, in Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Rhiwallon Llwyd ab Ithel, was 15 and his mother, Mrs. Rhiwallon Llwyd ab Ithel, was 12. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Mrs. Rhiwallon Fychan ap Rhiwallon Llwyd."},"et":{"about 1219–":"umbes 1219–Surnud","1219–Male":"1219–Surnud","1223–Female":"1223–Surnud","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1276–Female":"1276–Surnud","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1209–Female":"1209–Surnud","1205":"1205","about 1219":"umbes 1219","1245":"1245","1223":"1223","1276":"1276","1250":"1250","1209":"1209","1219":"1219","Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales","Trefrant, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Trefnant, Montgomery, Wales":"Trefnant, Clwyd, Wales, United Kingdom","Trefnant, Clwyd, Wales":"Trefnant, Clwyd, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1219–":"noin 1219–Kuollut","1219–Male":"1219–Kuollut","1223–Female":"1223–Kuollut","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1276–Female":"1276–Kuollut","1205–Male":"1205–Kuollut","1209–Female":"1209–Kuollut","1205":"1205","about 1219":"noin 1219","1245":"1245","1223":"1223","1276":"1276","1250":"1250","1209":"1209","1219":"1219","Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales","Trefrant, De